<br>
<br>
&quot;I am a level 19 druid. I had just heard a shout from the town crier telling one and all to come to the Millers humble farm in order to cleanse the plains(in WK). <br>
When I arrived to the scene there was an NPC (or rather GM) named Velarte Selire. In different land marks (as i passed by them) there were Braziers of Rodcet Nife, they looked like shadowmen..but had the trademark &quot;enchanters begging cup&quot; in their hands (if they have any). <br>
<br>
Soon Velarte Selire began shout, calling people to the millers and to help him cleanse the plains just as the town crier had. when he finally cut the the chase he produced a magical item called a smudge stick. He went over to a Brazier and put it to the creature, it then became a &quot;filled brazier&quot;. <br>
<br>
He then proceeded to give people the smudge sticks, instructing them to do the same as he had done. I was lucky enough to get one and hurredly gave one to the nearest Brazier at a farmhouse near the water. I was given some exp (actually a lot of exp for a quest) and a &quot;blessed ring of rodcet nife&quot;.<br>
<br>
It had +2 wis, 1ac and 1 charge of greater healing. When all the hassle had been done with putting the Smudge sticks into the Braziers the land rumbled, i started to praise Karana, just as i should. Fireworks exploded everywhere and i kept getting the message &quot;the plain begins to cast a spell&quot;.. <br>
<br>
The priest ran off eventually, commended me for my shouting of praise of karana, saying &quot;Sphan, mayhap you could teach your friend there what it is to follow Karana... striking down the one that engineered the healing of the lands of one's god is hardly commendable&quot;. Soon after he scolded the offending druid, ran off and started shouting about giving the news to the priests of Qeynos.Soon after the message came up saying :The air seems to pulsate as healing magical energy floods across the plains.&quot;<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
